            AMERICAN SOCIETY OF MECHANICAL ENGINEERS
Ocean, Offshore & Arctic Engineering Division - OMAE Houston Chapter

                          Presents

      DEEPWATER MARGINAL FIELD DEVELOPMENT SHORT COURSE

      28 February - 4 April, 2002:  6 Thursday Evenings

TIMES: 5:30 - 9:00 p.m.

LOCATION: SHELL BELLAIRE TECHNOLOGY CENTER AUDITORIUM, 3737 Bellaire
Boulevard (Inside Loop 610)

COST: $650.00 ASME members; $750.00 Non-members

Emphasis will be on providing insight into the technical and commercial
issues and solutions, as well as the decision-making processes, associated
with the development of marginal fields in deep water. The course shall
focus on actual issues that arise in the development of such fields and
shall draw on case studies and practical examples to highlight the
significance of the issues, identify the different potential courses of
action and demonstrate the reasoning behind each course of action being
selected.

Cost of the course includes session notes, publications, binders, and
sandwich dinner.

Each registrant who completes the course may request a Certificate of
Completion and CEU credit. Full refunds will be made for cancellations
received fifteen days prior to the first meeting of the seminar.
Cancellations received after that date are subject to a $150.00 cancellation
fee. No refunds will be made after the first meeting. Reservations are
transferable at no charge upon written notice received prior to the first
meeting.

A $100.00 refund will be made to each registrant who applies for ASME
membership before completion of the seminar.

Proceeds from OMAE Houston courses are used to fund scholarships at
universities for Mechanical Engineering students.

Registration fees must be paid prior to the first class meeting.

DEEPWATER MARGINAL FIELD DEVELOPMENT SHORT COURSE
February 28: Drivers - Major's view, Independent's view, Development
             Planning Overview
March 7:     Exploration & Reservoir Characterization; Drilling &
             Completions
March 14:    Floating Facilities, Subsea Systems & Flow Assurance; Facility
             Selection
March 21:    Export / Offtake; Construction & Installation
March 28:    HSE & Regulatory Issues; Operability;
April 4:     Marginal Field Development Case Studies

Course Outline: http://www.asme.org/divisions/ooaehtc/course_outline.html

Speakers include:
David Clarke, bp; Chuck Meloy, Kerr McGee; Lynn Whitworth, CSO-Aker; Ellen
Coopersmith, Decision Frameworks; Irv Brooks, Chevron; Jim Maher, CSO-Aker,
Paul Beer, Ocean Energy, Herve DeNaurois, TotalFinaElf; Chuck Stuebe,
Conoco, Todd Grove, ABS, and John Dagleish, Ocean Energy. Ocean, Offshore &
Arctic Engineering Division OMAE Houston Chapter

